&lt;p&gt;On our path to becoming the most visited online curated marketplace for special objects, our Engineering team is on a mission to deliver the best experience across our platforms by building best-in-class products for search &amp;amp; discovery, bidding, curation, logistics, payments, and support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re a scale-up with customer-facing challenges dealing with high-scale (75k auctions per week) and high traffic (more than 10 million visitors per month). As a Software Engineer, you’ll support one of our 3 verticals - Demand, Supply, or Fulfilment - improving and delivering product innovations for our platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in small, fully autonomous, and highly collaborative Agile teams, you will build scalable, maintainable, and resilient microservices and features. That&#39;s why we are looking for bold, curious and open developers! Are you ready to join?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build&lt;/strong&gt;: Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain and improve. You’ll be part of a team that is end-to-end responsible for their own microservices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate&lt;/strong&gt;: Work closely with product designers, product owners, front, back, and mobile engineers to share new ideas and make our processes even more efficient.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth&lt;/strong&gt;: Support our great engineering culture, by documenting and advocating for best development practices - constantly improving the quality of our products by fixing bugs and refactoring the code base where necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Boost your career by testing new technologies and participating in our Technical Week, a week dedicated to promoting creativity (after 2 product sprints), innovation, and knowledge sharing across domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Software Engineer, you already understand the full life cycle of web development and see opportunities in front of you. You&#39;re curious, solution-oriented and have a strong customer focus. Our stack is mainly focused around&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ruby&lt;/strong&gt;, however, if you’re passionate about learning new things then prior experience with Ruby is not essential. Next to this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least, 4+ years of experience with customer-facing products in related industries, e.g. e-commerce, fintechs, SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4+ years with software development, in specific OOP (object-oriented programming)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, implementing, and deploying backend services, with a focus on high availability, low latency, and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of APIs design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SQL and relational databases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable raising concerns, sharing new ideas, documenting, and finding opportunities for solution alternatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a passionate engineer, you bring these values to Catawiki:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You strive to be a great team player and don’t shy away from new challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are someone who takes initiative and is ready to jump in and help if needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess a &quot;growth mindset&quot; in which you take the initiative to further your personal skill set as a software developer, whether by learning new skills and/or technologies or by seeking new opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
