&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Leader:&lt;/strong&gt; Significant management experience with a track record of building accountable, high-performing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercially Savvy:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong business acumen with experience in P&amp;amp;L management, seller negotiation, and understanding customer needs. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Literate: &lt;/strong&gt;highly&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;skilled at interpreting metrics and turning them into insights that steer strategy and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clear Communicator &amp;amp; Influencer:&lt;/strong&gt; Skilled at engaging senior stakeholders and partners and aligning cross-functional teams in a matrix environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Affinity for Art:&lt;/strong&gt; Interested in the art world and passionate about its cultural value, without needing to be an art-market expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage internationally:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable and flexible to travel across Europe as required to connect with sellers, partners, and colleagues to strengthen Catawiki’s presence and network.&lt;/li&gt;
