&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Catawiki, every day brings the extraordinary! Whether it’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/583-sports-memorabilia&quot;&gt;Daniel Ricciardo’s Formula 1 Car&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/579-fossils&quot;&gt;Woolly Mammoth’s Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/l/10035805&quot;&gt;Lady Gaga&#39;s Jumpsuit&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/583-sports-memorabilia&quot;&gt;Usain Bolt’s running shoe&lt;/a&gt;, we encounter exceptional objects every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re a one-of-a-kind marketplace for buying and selling special objects! Each week we offer over 75,000 unique items in auction&lt;em&gt;,&lt;/em&gt; carefully curated by our passionate in-house experts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having sold over 20 million unique objects to date, we’re on a mission to become the world’s most popular destination for special objects. As a growing, diverse and sustainable scale-up, we proudly live by our core values:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking ownership and driving impact&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being open to change and feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being passionate about our mission and our customers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If these values resonate with you, we’d love to explore how you can join us on this exciting journey!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role and team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catawiki is building one of the most dynamic online destinations for exceptional objects. Our Galleries &amp;amp; Art Dealers Market (aka Secondary Market) division is at the heart of this ambition. We are seeking a proven category leader with strong management, commercial, and analytical skills to drive this category forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll oversee a diverse international team of experts, ensuring their knowledge and passion for art translate into scalable, data-driven, and high-quality offerings. Your mission is to design and execute a category strategy that delivers measurable growth, grounded in commercial insight, operational excellence, and strong cross-functional collaboration.&amp;nbsp;You will work with Sales, Marketing, Product, and Technology to drive performance, strengthen seller relationships, enhance user experience, while contributing to company-wide initiatives and empowering teams to deliver impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own and evolve category strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and execute the Secondary Market strategy in line with Catawiki’s vision and business objectives, ensuring measurable commercial impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive performance through data:&lt;/strong&gt; Monitor and interpret key metrics (GMV, conversion, lot quality, buyer engagement) and translate insights into clear, actionable improvements across pricing, selection, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and develop a high-performing team:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide clarity, coaching, and accountability to empower experts to deliver at scale and achieve measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maximise seller relationships and growth:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with Sales to acquire, negotiate with, and retain high-potential sellers, ensuring a consistent flow of quality supply and strong commercial relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage business performance:&lt;/strong&gt; Contribute to category-level P&amp;amp;L, balancing short-term efficiency with long-term strategic growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Leader:&lt;/strong&gt; Significant management experience with a track record of building accountable, high-performing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercially Savvy:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong business acumen with experience in P&amp;amp;L management, seller negotiation, and understanding customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Literate: &lt;/strong&gt;highly&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;skilled at interpreting metrics and turning them into insights that steer strategy and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clear Communicator &amp;amp; Influencer:&lt;/strong&gt; Skilled at engaging senior stakeholders and partners and aligning cross-functional teams in a matrix environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Affinity for Art:&lt;/strong&gt; Interested in the art world and passionate about its cultural value, without needing to be an art-market expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage internationally:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable and flexible to travel across Europe as required to connect with sellers, partners, and colleagues to strengthen Catawiki’s presence and network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where You’ll Be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is preferably based in the Netherlands, Portugal, or France and supports relocation. Remote work within Europe may be considered, although this is less desirable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text text-align-left &quot;&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love Working with Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create a Visible Impact&lt;/strong&gt; by working at scale in a global organisation that serves millions of customers across 80+ categories. In our flat structure, every role has a broad scope that directly impacts both our customers and the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn and Grow with Us&lt;/strong&gt; through our Learning &amp;amp; Development initiatives, which include clear development plans and mentorship programmes designed to support your career progression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Culture of Connection &lt;/strong&gt;defines us. We’re a passionate, diverse and collaborative team of 800+ Catawikains and 60+ nationalities, all coming together to build a one-of-a-kind marketplace. We foster an inclusive and queer-friendly work environment, committed to making every Catawikian feel welcomed and empowered. Whatever your story, we encourage you to bring your unique perspective to our team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Celebrate Life’s Moments &lt;/strong&gt;with us at Catawiki. When you join us, you’ll receive a €100 Catavoucher, and on each birthday, you&#39;ll get a €50 Catavoucher to celebrate. Enjoy an extra day off each year to &quot;Pursue Your Passion&quot;. We also recognise significant work anniversaries (3, 5, 8, 10 years) with additional time off, plus extra leave for life’s big moments like marriage, engagements, or moving house.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that benefits can vary by location. For specific information regarding what’s available in your country, please consult your recruiter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Offices and Way of Working&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vibrant offices in Amsterdam, Paris and Lisbon are designed to inspire and connect. Most Catawikians are within commuting distance of one of our offices and enjoy the flexibility of a hybrid work model. That said, some roles may be an exception: if the job description states that the position is fully remote or 100% office-based, that arrangement will apply instead.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interested?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply directly with an English CV and cover letter by submitting your information at the bottom of this page. By submitting your application you agree to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/conditions/applicant-privacy-policy.pdf&quot;&gt;Catawiki’s Applicant Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Catawiki, every day brings the extraordinary! Whether it’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/583-sports-memorabilia&quot;&gt;Daniel Ricciardo’s Formula 1 Car&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/579-fossils&quot;&gt;Woolly Mammoth’s Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/l/10035805&quot;&gt;Lady Gaga&#39;s Jumpsuit&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.catawiki.com/en/c/583-sports-memorabilia&quot;&gt;Usain Bolt’s running shoe&lt;/a&gt;, we encounter exceptional objects every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re a one-of-a-kind marketplace for buying and selling special objects! Each week we offer over 75,000 unique items in auction&lt;em&gt;,&lt;/em&gt; carefully curated by our passionate in-house experts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having sold over 20 million unique objects to date, we’re on a mission to become the world’s most popular destination for special objects. As a growing, diverse and sustainable scale-up, we proudly live by our core values:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking ownership and driving impact&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being open to change and feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being passionate about our mission and our customers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If these values resonate with you, we’d love to explore how you can join us on this exciting journey!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role and team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fuel the Future of Classic Car Sales!&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Exceptional cars deserve exceptional treatment,&amp;nbsp;and that’s where we come in. At Catawiki, we’re redefining how high-value, collector-grade vehicles are discovered, evaluated, and sold online. We&#39;re a tight-knit, high-performing team of automotive experts based in the Netherlands and Italy, and we’re on the lookout for someone who’s not only passionate about cars but driven by commercial impact. This role is not just about admiring classic cars; it&#39;s about making them move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Classic Car Expert, you’ll be working with high-value lots and a targeted, specific buyer audience. We’re obsessed with quality and detail, whether it&#39;s a rare Alfa Romeo or a perfectly preserved Porsche. Each of us brings deep brand knowledge, some of us breathe Italian heritage, others know the German precision scene like the back of their hand. But beyond the passion, we also know what matters most: getting the deal done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We combine expertise with execution. We help sellers present their cars in the best possible way, but we don’t just &quot;list and hope.&quot; We screen every lot with a commercial lens, we push for promotional and themed auctions, and we ask ourselves: &lt;em&gt;Will this sell? And to whom?&lt;/em&gt; If we don’t have the answer, we ask each other. We trust our collective knowledge more than any tool, and that collaboration fuels our performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes this role exciting?&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;You’ll focus on growing the category through new leads from currently unsupported and/or underserved markets (Spain/Portugal) and by reactivating dormant sellers. You’ll bring your own network and build trust with new clients, staying sharp on market trends and spotting what’s next before it hits the mainstream. From fairs and local events to one-on-one phone calls, your day will be a mix of deep automotive conversation and smart sales thinking. It’s a dynamic, hybrid environment where autonomy meets teamwork, and if the opportunity arises, we even meet in person to keep the energy high.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the challenges?&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;We operate in a fast-moving space, and not every lot is a guaranteed success. Our challenge is to build curated auctions that excite buyers, create urgency, and convert. We’re also building bridges between digital and traditional — helping sellers and buyers trust an online auction model for high-value vehicles. That means being responsive, professional, and always ahead of the curve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In short, we&#39;re car lovers, but even more — we’re deal makers! If you can tell the story behind a car, but also sell it with conviction... if you’re comfortable working with targets and inspired by international growth... if you&#39;re ready to bring your own spark to a strong team — then you might be the one we’re looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expand Untapped Markets&lt;/strong&gt;: Proactively pursue new leads from unsupported or underserved countries, turning them into active seller portfolios and opening new commercial frontiers for Catawiki’s classic car category.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Revive and Grow Seller Relationships:&lt;/strong&gt; Grow existing seller portfolios and re-engage past sellers by leveraging your automotive expertise, sales instinct, and a personalized approach to relationship management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver Commercial Results:&lt;/strong&gt; You work confidently with targets and are motivated by outcomes. You leverage your personal network to secure high-value cars and commercial deals that contribute directly to GMV.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curate High-Quality Auctions&lt;/strong&gt;: You screen incoming lots with care and commercial focus, ensuring auctions are filled with cars that resonate with our buyer audience — both in quality and story.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create Story-Driven Auctions:&lt;/strong&gt; You bring creativity to the table by proposing themed auctions and promotional lots, using storytelling and strategic thinking to attract new interest and deepen buyer engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support Cross-Category Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; While your focus is classic cars, you’re ready to support the motorcycle category when needed — contributing your insight and energy to help the broader automotive team succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network Activator&lt;/strong&gt;: You bring a strong personal network of sellers, collectors, and dealers to Catawiki, expanding our supply of high-quality classic cars and unlocking new commercial opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales-First Mindset&lt;/strong&gt;: You love beautiful cars, but you know this is a business — you focus on selling, not just showcasing. Your decisions are driven by commercial value, buyer demand, and closing potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Expander&lt;/strong&gt;: You actively grow Catawiki’s footprint in underdeveloped countries and markets, identifying local opportunities, onboarding sellers, and turning gaps into growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Energiser&lt;/strong&gt;: You inject fresh perspective and drive into the team, motivating 3 classic car experts and 2 motorcycle experts through collaboration, knowledge sharing, and a passion for performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Contributor&lt;/strong&gt;: You think beyond listings — identifying untapped segments, proposing structural improvements, and helping shape our approach to classic cars across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automotive Enthusiast with Impact&lt;/strong&gt;: Your passion for cars is matched by your hunger to deliver results. You understand the vehicles, but you also understand what makes them sell — and you act on it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native Spanish Speaker, Good English speaking &amp;amp; Fine understanding/speaking of Portuguese.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge about Automotive and especially Classic Cars &amp;amp; Youngtimers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing network of sellers / business that you can bring to Catawiki&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial mindset, sales / negotiation skills and outbound call experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mediocre knowledge of computer programs, dashboards &amp;amp; CRM / sales systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with KPI’s &amp;amp; Targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to learn and educate sales tips &amp;amp; tricks via literature, podcasts &amp;amp; videos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open to AI and embrace the benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to communicate with different levels of mainly sellers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where You’ll Be&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based in Portugal, preferably in the Lisbon area, with a work-from-home arrangement and the opportunity to visit our office in Lisbon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text text-align-left &quot;&gt;
