&lt;p&gt;If these values resonate with you, we’d love to explore how you can join us on this exciting journey!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Catawiki Interiors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catawiki Interiors is one of Catawiki’s four core business units, alongside Luxury, Collectibles, and Art. We are a passionate team of 45+ professionals working every day to bring the excitement of auctions to interior lovers and collectors across Europe—whether it’s a Tiffany lamp or an iconic Eames chair.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Interiors business unit is built around three core categories: Design &amp;amp; Vintage, Home Decor, and Classic Interiors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Interiors Sales Team at Catawiki is a fast-paced, impact-driven group of commercial talents powering the success of some of Europe’s most passionate sellers. We operate with a strong sense of ownership— each Account Manager drives their own category-focused portfolio across Europe, whether it’s Design &amp;amp; Vintage, Home Decor or Classic Interiors, with the mindset of running “a business within the business”.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To fuel this growth, each Account Manager partners closely with a Key Business Developer, forming a powerful duo that combines strategic seller acquisition with long-term account success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take full responsibility for our seller performance, shaping strategies, spotting growth opportunities, and executing with precision. Market knowledge, sales acumen, and creative thinking are our tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Collaboration is core to our culture—we share, challenge, and celebrate as one team.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Our mission: make Catawiki the leading destination for passionate buyers and sellers of exceptional interior pieces.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Catawiki Interiors Sales Team&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Key Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the growth of our &lt;strong&gt;Design &amp;amp; Vintage&lt;/strong&gt; category across Europe. You’ll fully own a portfolio of international sellers and act as the commercial driver behind its continued success.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a strategic and entrepreneurial mindset, you’ll identify opportunities, build tailored growth plans, and execute initiatives that deliver performance and profitability. In close partnership with the Category Lead, you’ll help shape and deliver category strategy. Alongside your category experts and business developer, you’ll implement scalable commercial actions and maximize seller potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From commercial negotiations to long-term partnership building, you’ll play a key role in expanding the reach and impact of Design &amp;amp; Vintage at Catawiki. You’ll approach your portfolio like your own business—with the autonomy and accountability to shape its growth. This position will report to the Team Lead. Remote or hybrid work options are available depending on your location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Key Account Manager, you are &lt;strong&gt;fully accountable for your seller portfolio’s performance&lt;/strong&gt;, with clear impact across GMV, supply quality, and seller retention. Your responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seller Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Build strong relationships with sellers. Coach them on performance drivers such as pricing strategy, supply quality, and customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Planning:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and implement medium- and long-term growth strategies, aligned with category goals and commercial objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Reviews &amp;amp; Insights:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct regular reviews with sellers. Use performance data to identify opportunities and drive commercial actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead strategic sales conversations with sellers, often alongside experts. Deliver clear action plans that drive measurable improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High-Impact Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Work cross-functionally with experts and business developers to support marketing campaigns and drive joint initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Management Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain close engagement with your sellers across all touchpoints: meetings, calls, events, and digital tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovation &amp;amp; Growth Activation:&lt;/strong&gt; Spot opportunities in the market and translate them into commercial initiatives that push the portfolio forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in sales, business development, or account management roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high level of energy and enthusiasm. You’re excited to hit the ground running and bring positive energy to the team from day one!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills across all channels—whether in person, by phone, or over email&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English is required; Italian is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to build, grow, and manage strategic relationships with commercial impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking paired with a sharp commercial mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective negotiation skills to secure profitable, scalable deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of autonomy, strong organizational skills, and a proactive, self-starting attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for interiors, design, or collecting is a definite plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel regularly across Europe to connect with sellers and attend events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tech-savvy:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using CRM systems like HubSpot or similar is mandatory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident using Google Workspace (Sheets, Slides);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our offices and way of working - Hybrid or Full remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; We have vibrant offices in Amsterdam, Paris, and our newest location in Lisbon. The majority of our employees live within commuting distance of one of these hubs and follow a hybrid work model. This typically means being in the office 2 out of 5 days—or around 40% of the time—to collaborate, connect, and foster team spirit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remote&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Depending on your location, we also offer the possibility to work fully remotely.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text text-align-left &quot;&gt;
